qc.pdf` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_QFvrIhksnhVCigSKfnPbSTV1", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{}", "name": "list_workdir"}}, {"id": "call_0W9Z7PMh5TrrpMFDIAxVok8G", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}", "name": "list_workdir", "tool_call_id": "call_QFvrIhksnhVCigSKfnPbSTV1"}, {"role": "tool", "content": "# Real R-task: chipseq_plot_macs_qc\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `snakemake-workflows-chipseq` (family: `chipseq`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given three MACS2-style narrowPeak BED files under `input/`:\n  - `sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak`\n  - `sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak`\n  - `sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak`\n\nEach file has 10 tab-delimited columns (chrom, start, end, name, pileup, strand,\nfold, -log10(pvalue), -log10(qvalue), summit).\n\nProduce two files under `output/`:\n  - `macs_qc_summary.tsv`: per-sample summary statistics (Min/1stQu/Median/Mean/\n    3rdQu/Max plus `num_peaks`, `measure`, `sample`) for `fold`, `-log10(qvalue)`,\n    `-log10(pvalue)`, and `length` (end-start).\n  - `macs_qc.pdf`: a multi-page PDF with the peak count barplot and three violin\n    plots (length on log10, fold on log2, FDR / pvalue on linear -log10).\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/macs_qc.pdf` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: macs_qc.pdf, macs_qc_summary.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n", "name": "read_text_file", "tool_call_id": "call_0W9Z7PMh5TrrpMFDIAxVok8G"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_jFfQyUA6ekMUgJKO1XJGQF4a", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"- Read the three narrowPeak files from the input directory.\\n- Calculate summary statistics for each sample: Min, 1stQu, Median, Mean, 3rdQu, Max for `fold`, `-log10(qvalue)`, `-log10(pvalue)`, and `length` (end-start).\\n- Create a TSV file `macs_qc_summary.tsv` with columns: `num_peaks`, `measure`, `sample`.\\n- Generate a PDF `macs_qc.pdf` with:\\n  - A barplot of peak counts per sample.\\n  - Violin plots for `length` (log10 scale), `fold` (log2 scale), and `-log10(pvalue)`/`-log10(qvalue)` (linear scale).\\n- Save outputs in the output directory.\\n- Validate the presence of `macs_qc.pdf` and `macs_qc_summary.tsv` in the output directory.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (638 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_jFfQyUA6ekMUgJKO1XJGQF4a"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_lDZ3H6NDMwhUN2bhIHeaIk0x", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"# Load necessary libraries\\nlibrary(ggplot2)\\nlibrary(dplyr)\\nlibrary(tidyr)\\nlibrary(ggpubr)\\n\\n# Define function to read and process narrowPeak files\\nprocess_narrowPeak <- function(file_path, sample_name) {\\n  data <- read.table(file_path, header = FALSE, sep = \\\"\\\\t\\\")\\n  colnames(data) <- c(\\\"chrom\\\", \\\"start\\\", \\\"end\\\", \\\"name\\\", \\\"pileup\\\", \\\"strand\\\", \\\"fold\\\", \\\"-log10(pvalue)\\\", \\\"-log10(qvalue)\\\", \\\"summit\\\")\\n  data$length <- data$end - data$start\\n  data$sample <- sample_name\\n  return(data)\\n}\\n\\n# Read data\\nsampleA <- process_narrowPeak('input/sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak', 'sampleA')\\nsampleB <- process_narrowPeak('input/sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak', 'sampleB')\\nsampleC <- process_narrowPeak('input/sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak', 'sampleC')\\n\\n# Combine data\\nall_data <- bind_rows(sampleA, sampleB, sampleC)\\n\\n# Calculate summary statistics\\nsummary_stats <- all_data %>%\\n  gather(key = \\\"measure\\\", value = \\\"value\\\", fold, `-log10(pvalue)`, `-log10(qvalue)`, length) %>%\\n  group_by(sample, measure) %>%\\n  summarise(\\n    Min = min(value),\\n    `1stQu` = quantile(value, 0.25),\\n    Median = median(value),\\n    Mean = mean(value),\\n    `3rdQu` = quantile(value, 0.75),\\n    Max = max(value),\\n    num_peaks = n()\\n  )\\n\\n# Write summary statistics to TSV\\nwrite.table(summary_stats, 'output/macs_qc_summary.tsv', sep = '\\\\t', row.names = FALSE)\\n\\n# Plotting\\npdf('output/macs_qc.pdf')\\n\\n# Barplot of peak counts\\npeak_counts <- all_data %>% group_by(sample) %>% summarise(num_peaks = n())\\nggplot(peak_counts, aes(x = sample, y = num_peaks)) +\\n  geom_bar(stat = \\\"identity\\\") +\\n  theme_minimal() +\\n  ggtitle(\\\"Peak Counts per Sample\\\")\\n\\n# Violin plots\\n# Length\\nggplot(all_data, aes(x = sample, y = log10(length))) +\\n  geom_violin() +\\n  theme_minimal() +\\n  ggtitle(\\\"Peak Length Distribution (log10)\\\")\\n\\n# Fold\\nggplot(all_data, aes(x = sample, y = log2(fold))) +\\n  geom_violin() +\\n  theme_minimal() +\\n  ggtitle(\\\"Fold Enrichment Distribution (log2)\\\")\\n\\n# -log10(pvalue)\\nggplot(all_data, aes(x = sample, y = `-log10(pvalue)`)) +\\n  geom_violin() +\\n  theme_minimal() +\\n  ggtitle(\\\"-log10(pvalue) Distribution\\\")\\n\\ndev.off()\\n\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": fal